"0x23800\"\r\n        }\r\n      ],\r\n      \"current_model\": [\r\n        \"BLE verifies the outer MI.TFOTA package and streams BMS/VCU verbatim to the downstream bootloader\",\r\n        \"Downstream secure packets use AES-128 over the first 16 bytes of the 32-byte session key at 0x002c1a1c\",\r\n        \"Downstream 0x5a secure-packet codec is mapped: TX 0x020dc17c computes CRC over plaintext header/body before body encryption at offset 0x04; RX 0x020dbfd8 decrypts, rebuilds plaintext length, verifies CRC, and dispatches decrypted body byte 1 as secure command\",\r\n        \"secure_send ABI contract is explicit (com_analysis/mcu_secure_send_arg_contract.json): r0=node_id, r1=secure_command, r2=payload_ptr(nullable), r3=payload_len; header bytes map as [0]=0x5a, [1]=node_id, [5]=command, len=payload+8, consistent across VCU/BMS call-sites\",\r\n        \"Session/auth path is Brightway-style ECC: command 0x12 SN sync, 0x13 ECDH/public key, 0x14 signed challenge, 0x1f signed identity auth; topic table maps command 0x06 to signed restart.set.*.comm and command 0x07 to signed reset.set.*.comm\",\r\n        \"Caller graph splits auth policy: 0x020df3a0 publishes command-0x13 flag-0 sessionkey.rec, 0x020de9d8 chains command-0x13 flag-1 refresh with command-0x14 signed auth from identity/session maintenance, and 0x020defe8 is command-0x1f fallback\",\r\n        \"Brightway auth-state gating is now explicit: refresh/auth completion, identity-fallback enablement, and retry warmup use separate state bytes/counters (0x002c1e88, 0x002c1e89, 0x002c1e8c), and mode-1 maintenance path clears live session RAM before returning\",\r\n        \"Persistent key lifecycle is now explicit: privkey.rec (0x20), pubkey.rec (0x40), bindflag.rec (0x01), and sessionkey.rec (0x20) each have distinct load/write/use roles, with sessionkey.rec reloaded into RAM separately from persistent identity records\",\r\n        \"Layer-4 orchestration split is now exact: 0x020df454 and 0x020df56c are distinct high-level callers over three lower lanes (session generation, refresh+signed-auth maintenance, and fallback identity auth), and 0x020de9d8 is reached as mode-2 refresh/auth from both callers\",\r\n        \"Layer-4 auth status surface is now explicit: bit helper 0x020dbf50 updates a shared status word, bit 0x11 marks session-generation failure, bit 0x10 marks fallback identity-auth failure, class 0x101 publishes fault states, class 0x100 fans out wrapper return status, and class 0x601 publishes inverse identity-gate state\",\r\n        \"Bind/provisioning command-0x14 taxonomy is now explicit: direct payload path 0x020dd630 and record-driven SN sync 0x020de8d0 both feed the same 0x14-byte identity/SN buffer for command 0x12; command 0x14 flag 1 is maintenance refresh auth via 0x020de7d0, while command 0x14 flag 0 is after-sales Unbind auth via 0x020de21c\",\r\n        \"Layer-4 auth public entry surface is now explicit: the BLE auth_binding domain exposes 8 public topics covering restart/reset signed commands, two SN-provisioning feeds, and the staged passwd/bind/unbind session-auth lanes, so all major auth/session lanes now have known public BLE entry\",\r\n        \"Session bootstrap contract is now explicit: sessionkey.rec reuse is gated by a shape-check/readiness probe, startup path preloads sessionkey.rec into live RAM before fresh session generation, and persisted session reuse is coordinated with on-demand regeneration instead of being an opaque preload side effect\",\r\n        \"Receive dispatch table at 0x021733b8/RAM 0x002c1a74 maps decrypted secure replies: cmd 0x13 -> 0x020dc3d8, cmd 0x14 -> 0x020dc414, cmd 0x1f -> 0x020dc49c class-0x500 wait records; cmd 0x06/0x07 are status-only class-0x100 handlers\",\r\n        \"Downstream BMS/VCU records are now split structurally: BMS has a repeated 16-byte fill block plus a unique 16-byte footer at file 0x18c00, while VCU has a 0xa000 sealed payload plus a cstd tail at file 0x23000\",\r\n        \"BMS record topology is now explicit at 0x60 cadence: 1010 body records + 34 fill records, with repetition at 16-byte block granularity (53 repeated non-fill block values) and 88 records containing at least one repeated block\",\r\n        \"VCU main structure is now explicit: 40 x 0x400 chunks (0xa000) with entropy about 7.99, chi2 about 449.56, 0 repeated 16-byte blocks, and cstd tail immediately following at file 0x23000\",\r\n        \"Container cipher constraints are now consolidated: BMS supports ECB-like per-block/per-record-key class while CTR/CBC and static app-key classes are ruled out; VCU cstd pair 0/1 supports shared low2-plane/keystream-like constraint\",\r\n        \"VCU cstd field topology is now explicit: 6 records x 0x60, pair 0/1 has hamming 243 with low2 XOR all-zero and per-lane hamming [75,74,94], while no stable 4-byte subfield exists across all 6 records\",\r\n        \"BLE-side MCU outer signature failure branch is mapped as a lab-only patch plan at app 0x2793 address 0x020f421c: old 40f0a280 -> new 00bf00bf; no bypass binary was built in this pass\",\r\n        \"Visible-metadata keyed MAC hypotheses are negative: AES-CMAC, HMAC, and keyed BLAKE2 over obvious BMS/VCU ranges did not match the full BMS footer or VCU cstd check word\",\r\n        \"Outer MI.TFOTA verify readout is mapped: 0x020f3600 returns parser/cert/signature error codes and 0x020f421c is the caller failure branch after cmp r0,#0\",\r\n        \"Downstream readout/status path is now split from OTA transfer: OtaQueryAck command 0x04 is the primary mutation-test verify readout, while 0xca/0xcb/0xcc form a separate BLE RAM receive/readback stream into 0x02212000; caller search shows 0xcb in mible_mcu_nvm_write is only an internal state marker, not secure command 0xcb\",\r\n        \"BLE business-logic topic map is now explicit and reproducible: all 36 MQTT-style topics are fully characterized across OTA/auth/VCU/BMS domains, with direct secure-command mapping for 32 topics, orchestration command-set mapping for 3 handlers, and one explicit cache-only non-command path (ChargeTime.get.bms.comm) tracked as command-gap but not unresolved\",\r\n        \"BLE orchestration policy layer is now machine-readable: unresolved handlers are split into orchestration_indirect versus cache_only classes, yielding command-or-better coverage 35/36 (97.2%) without overstating direct secure-send evidence\",\r\n        \"BLE handler-local call-profile evidence is now reproducible: for the four non-direct handlers, ChargeTime.get.bms.comm (0x020de434) shows publish-helper calls plus class-0x500 immediate and no direct call to secure-send 0x020dc17c, while passwd/bind/shutdown remain orchestration-indirect\",\r\n        \"ChargeTime.get upstream dispatch path is now explicitly evidenced: call-xref scan finds zero direct call-sites to 0x020de434, while nearby dispatcher code loads handler pointer from topic-table slot [+0x24], node from [+0x20], and invokes via blx r2 in a 0x24-entry loop with 0x28 stride\",\r\n        \"BLE topic dispatcher 0x020de48c is now mapped as a table-driven indirection layer: loop bound/stride match 36-entry topic table (0x24/0x28), handler invocation is indirect via blx r2, and dispatcher body has no direct secure-send call to 0x020dc17c\",\r\n        \"ChargeTime.get handler 0x020de434 micro-path is now explicit: cbz guard exits early when context is null, non-null path publishes class-0x500 length-6 cached payload via 0x020d6640/0x020d6af8, and no direct secure-send call appears in handler body\",\r\n        \"BLE evidence layer is now consolidated in a single index: direct/orchestration/cache-only coverage and the full ChargeTime chain (call-profile + upstream xref + dispatcher map + handler micro-path) are synchronized as one machine-readable artifact\",\r\n        \"A runtime closure plan for the final BLE gap is now explicit: ChargeTime.get requires topic-window packet capture, dispatcher/handler trace, downstream command histogram, and baseline subtraction, with formal promote/keep decision rules and stop conditions\",\r\n        \"BLE business-logic closure workflow is now execution-ready: ChargeTime observation template defines 3 runs and 12 capture fields with verdict rules, and BLE modification acceptance workflow has a 4-test hardware matrix (baseline, valid signed patch, invalid-auth negative, repeatability)\",\r\n        \"ChargeTime run evaluation is now deterministic: observation JSONL rows are scored into pending/keep_cache_only/promote_to_command_level_candidate verdict classes using completed-run and baseline-delta/command-evidence rules\",\r\n        \"BLE handler-local call matrix now covers all 36 topics, with local direct secure-send in 30 handlers and publish-helper paths in 34; one-hop/two-hop reachability refines wrapper confidence and recovers Bind via 0x020de8d0 -> 0x020dc17c chain\",\r\n        \"Two mapped topics (Unbind.set.vcu.comm, heartbeat.comm) currently remain without <=2-hop secure-send path evidence, so their command-level confidence is weaker than direct/wrapper-confirmed topics until deeper-hop or alternate evidence is added\",\r\n        \"Targeted deep reachability probe to depth 6 remains negative for Unbind.set.vcu.comm and heartbeat.comm (no call-graph path to 0x020dc17c), so these two mapped topics stay conservative-confidence until non-call or deeper evidence appears\",\r\n        \"Multi-hop BLE reachability is now quantified at depths 1/2/4/6/8/10: secure-send path coverage rises 30 -> 31 -> 32 and plateaus, with mapped no-path topics reduced to three by depth 10 (Unbind.set.vcu.comm, shutdown.vehicle.hmi, heartbeat.comm)\",\r\n        \"Alternative lane model is now explicit for depth-10 no-path topics: 3 are local_control_or_cache (ChargeTime.get.bms.comm, Unbind.set.vcu.comm, heartbeat.comm) and 1 is orchestration_indirect_no_path (shutdown.vehicle.hmi), keeping business-logic mapping complete without overstating direct command paths\",\r\n        \"BLE command-core 0x020db92c is mapped: command 1 starts/reset state, 3 accounts host fragments, 4 verifies BMS/VCU, 5 activates, and 6 handles transfer header, final MI.TFOTA marker, and verbatim TranData streaming\",\r\n        \"BLE OTA command-core public entry surface is now complete: five wrappers cover commands 1..6 with stable state tokens 0x60/0x77/0x8d/0xa3/0xbf->0xcb, and transfer is the only multi-command public path\",\r\n        \"BLE OTA command-core progress contract is now exact: denominator is 0x23800 = transfer header 0x800 + BMS 0x18800 + VCU 0x0a800; request/erase bootstrap accounts for the header once, and 140 TranData chunks of 0x400 land exactly on the same denominator at transfer completion\",\r\n        \"BLE OTA command-core field lifecycle is now explicit: header gate 0x002c9a5c and header shadow 0x002c9e64 are separated from final-marker state; commands 1..6 now have a field transition model for gate, marker, chunk indexes, and progress counters\",\r\n        \"Brightway-style session key lifecycle is now explicit: live transport key RAM is 0x002c1a1c (0x20 bytes stored, first 0x10 used as AES-128 key), reset/store/pointer helpers are identified, command 0x13 flag 0 derives the live key via ECDH, and the 0x5a secure packet codec consumes that RAM buffer rather than persistent key records directly\",\r\n        \"Android-to-BLE capture mapping is reconstructed: UUID 0x18 carries 71 image fragments of 0x800 bytes matching fw[0:0x23800], then a separate 000000000600 final group carries the 0x539-byte MI.TFOTA marker/TLV/cert/signature tail; prefix plus tail matches the full package 0x23d39 exactly\",\r\n        \"BLE capture post-tail status timeline is mapped: UUID17 acknowledgement pattern 020300XX00 covers all fragment indexes 1..72, confirming 0203004800 as the fragment-72 tail ACK; then command-6 completion candidate 06000401000000, uuid1b status payload, and final uuid1c TLV 010432303331 decode to ASCII 2031 as an app-visible success/version anchor\",\r\n        \"BLE transfer contract is now cross-capture reproducible: both local extracted captures reconstruct the full package byte-for-byte with identical 71+1 group shape, complete ACK coverage 1..72, and stable cmd6 phase-4 completion marker after tail transfer\",\r\n        \"Mutation-to-capture targeting is mapped: all 11 same-size mutation payload bytes are inside the captured UUID 0x18 prefix, and each variant has an associated transfer-header CRC32 update point in fragment 1/subpacket 1\",\r\n        \"Capture packet patching is mapped: the 11 mutation variants expand to 22 exact BLE WRITE packet edits, covering header CRC32 plus payload byte for each test; all expected old bytes match the captured packet bytes\",\r\n        \"Downstream OTA status ladder is mapped: erase uses OtaCmd byte 0 with OtaQuery statuses 0=continue and 1=success; verify uses OtaCmd byte 1 with statuses 3=continue and 4=success; update/activate uses OtaCmd byte 2; wrapper timeout/invalid node is 0x0a and VCU all-continue poll timeout is 0x07\",\r\n        \"BMS/VCU polling asymmetry is now explicit: BMS all-continue for all 10 erase/verify polls falls through to the VCU phase, while VCU all-continue for all 10 polls returns poll_timeout 0x07; current full-transfer capture proves command-6 completion/final 2031 but does not expose a full command-4 verify loop\",\r\n        \"Mutation readout plan is mapped: 11 mutation variants are joined with exact BLE WRITE packet edits, downstream node, target class, expected OtaQuery readout, and accepted/rejected interpretation; required observation fields are outer verify, request/erase/transfer/verify statuses, final command return, and app-visible TLV\",\r\n        \"BLE/MCU consistency audit is reproducible: 38/38 checks pass across BLE auth, MCU package, BLE capture, UART CCM trace, mutation targets, packet patch list, mutation readout plan, hardware lab bundle, supplemental mutation plan, status ladder, command-core/readou